Third Department,

January, 1951.

(January 10, 1951.) In the Matter of the Claim of Janet Lane, Respondent. Edward Corsi, as Industrial Commissioner, Appellant.

Motion to withdraw and discontinue appeal from a decision of the Unemployment Insurance Appeal Board, dated June 2, 1950. Motion granted, without costs. Present — Foster, P. J., Heffeman, Brewster, Bergan and Coon, JJ.
